    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">SEPCO Bill Check Online — Sukkur Electricity Bill 2026</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4">The <strong>Sukkur Electric Power Company (SEPCO)</strong> supplies electricity to nine districts of upper Sindh — from Sukkur and Larkana to Jacobabad and Khairpur. With more than <strong>1.2 million consumers</strong> across one of Pakistan's harshest summer climates, getting your monthly SEPCO bill on time matters. Instead of waiting for the printed bill to arrive by post (which can take 5–10 days in rural Sindh), you can now check your SEPCO bill online in under 30 seconds — and this guide walks you through every step.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Answer: Visit <a href="/sepco-bill/" class="underline">pakistanbill.online/sepco-bill/</a>, type your <strong>14-digit SEPCO reference number</strong> (printed on the top-right of any previous bill), and your current month's bill appears instantly. You can download a PDF copy, check the due date, and verify the amount — all for free, with no login.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is SEPCO and Who Does It Serve?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">SEPCO was formed in 1998 when WAPDA's Sukkur region was corporatized as part of Pakistan's power-sector reform program. The company is headquartered in Sukkur and operates under the regulatory oversight of NEPRA (National Electric Power Regulatory Authority). Its license area covers <strong>nine districts of northern Sindh</strong>:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Sukkur</strong> — including Rohri, Pano Aqil, Saleh Pat</li>
      <li><strong>Larkana</strong> — including Ratodero, Dokri</li>
      <li><strong>Khairpur</strong> — including Kot Diji, Faiz Ganj</li>
      <li><strong>Shikarpur</strong> — including Khanpur, Garhi Yasin</li>
      <li><strong>Jacobabad</strong> — including Thul, Kandhkot</li>
      <li><strong>Ghotki</strong> — including Mirpur Mathelo, Daharki</li>
      <li><strong>Kashmore</strong> — including Kandhkot, Tangwani</li>
      <li><strong>Kamber-Shahdadkot</strong> — including Warah, Miro Khan</li>
      <li><strong>Dadu (partial)</strong> — some eastern tehsils fall under SEPCO</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If you live in any of these districts, your electricity is supplied by SEPCO — not HESCO (which covers Hyderabad and lower Sindh). Knowing this matters because the two companies have separate billing systems, helplines, and reference number formats.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: How to Check Your SEPCO Bill Online</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Checking your SEPCO bill takes less than a minute if you have your reference number handy. Follow these exact steps:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-4 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Find your 14-digit SEPCO reference number.</strong> Look at any previous SEPCO bill — the reference number is printed in bold on the <strong>top-right section</strong>, labeled "Ref. No." or "Reference No.", directly above the barcode. It contains only digits (no letters, no dashes).</li>
      <li><strong>Open the SEPCO bill checker.</strong> Go to <a href="/sepco-bill/" class="text-primary-600 underline">pakistanbill.online/sepco-bill/</a> on any device — mobile, tablet, or desktop. No app installation required.</li>
      <li><strong>Enter the reference number carefully.</strong> Type all 14 digits. Double-check for typos — a single wrong digit will return "no bill found". You can paste the number if you copied it from an e-bill.</li>
      <li><strong>Click "Check Bill".</strong> Your current month's SEPCO bill loads within 2–3 seconds. The page displays: consumer name, address, billing month, units consumed, total amount, due date, and any arrears or late-payment surcharges.</li>
      <li><strong>Download or print the PDF.</strong> Click the "Download PDF" button to save a duplicate copy of your bill. This PDF is identical to the printed bill and is accepted at all banks and retail shops for payment.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Information Shows on Your SEPCO Bill?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">When you check your SEPCO bill online, you'll see the following details — all of which are also printed on the physical bill that arrives by post:</p>
    <div class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-400 font-mono rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs mb-2">// SEPCO Bill — Key Sections</p>
      <p>┌─────────────────────────────────────┐</p>
      <p>│  SEPCO Electricity Bill                  │</p>
      <p>│  ┌────────────────────────────────┐    │</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-300">│  │ <strong>Ref. No: 01234567890123</strong>    │    │ ← 14-digit</p>
      <p>│  │ Consumer: [Your Name]          │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Address: [Your Address]        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Month: June 2026               │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Reading Date: 12-June-2026     │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Units Consumed: 320 kWh        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Total Amount: Rs. 12,450       │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Due Date: 28-June-2026         │    │</p>
      <p>│  └────────────────────────────────┘    │</p>
      <p>│  [████████ BARCODE ████████]            │</p>
      <p>└─────────────────────────────────────┘</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Pay close attention to three fields: <strong>Units Consumed</strong> (so you can compare with your meter reading), <strong>Total Amount</strong> (verify there are no surprise charges), and <strong>Due Date</strong> (late payment adds 5–10% surcharge under SEPCO's tariff schedule).</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How to Pay Your SEPCO Bill</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Once you've checked your bill online, you have several payment options. Pick whichever is most convenient — the bill amount is the same at all channels:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Method</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Where</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Fee</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Time</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3">JazzCash</td><td class="p-3">Mobile app / USSD</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">EasyPaisa</td><td class="p-3">Mobile app / USSD</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">Bank mobile apps</td><td class="p-3">HBL, UBL, MCB, Alfalah, Meezan</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">1Bill vouchers</td><td class="p-3">Any retailer / ATM</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30–50</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
