          <tr><td class="p-3">NADRA e-Sahulat</td><td class="p-3">Any NADRA center</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">SEPCO office</td><td class="p-3">Sukkur HQ or circle offices</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">After payment, keep the receipt for at least 3 months in case of dispute. Payments made before 4 PM are usually reflected in SEPCO's system the next business day.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">SEPCO Customer Service & Complaints</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">If your bill shows an incorrect amount, your meter is faulty, or there's a power outage, SEPCO provides several complaint channels:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Helpline:</strong> 118 (toll-free from any landline in Sindh) or 071-9210055 from mobile</li>
      <li><strong>Complaint cell:</strong> 071-5613000 (operational 24/7 for power-fault complaints)</li>
      <li><strong>Online complaint:</strong> Submit at <code class="bg-neutral-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">sepco.com.pk</code> under "Complaints" — you'll receive a tracking number</li>
      <li><strong>WhatsApp:</strong> SEPCO does not officially use WhatsApp for complaints — beware of scams</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> info@sepco.com.pk for general queries; complaints cell has separate email</li>
      <li><strong>Visit:</strong> SEPCO HQ, Minara Road, Sukkur — or your nearest circle office</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Always mention your 14-digit reference number when registering a complaint — without it, the customer service representative cannot locate your account. Take a photo of any in-person complaint receipt for follow-up.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips to Avoid Common SEPCO Bill Issues</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Always keep last month's bill.</strong> It contains your reference number, which you'll need to check future bills online if the printed bill doesn't arrive.</li>
      <li><strong>Take a meter reading photo</strong> on the date mentioned in your bill as "Reading Date". If SEPCO's reading is higher than your actual meter, you have evidence for a correction request.</li>
      <li><strong>Pay before the 25th of each month</strong> to avoid late-payment surcharge and crowd at banks on due date.</li>
      <li><strong>Use the "Average Bill" facility</strong> only as a last resort if your meter is broken — actual readings are always cheaper in the long run because averages are based on the last 3 months and may overestimate.</li>
      <li><strong>Check the FPA (Fuel Price Adjustment) line item.</strong> If it suddenly jumps, that's not SEPCO's fault — it's a government-passed-through charge based on international fuel prices.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check SEPCO bill online?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Go to pakistanbill.online/sepco-bill/ and enter your 14-digit SEPCO reference number. Your Sukkur electricity bill loads instantly — free, no login, no app required.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Which districts does SEPCO cover?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">SEPCO (Sukkur Electric Power Company) covers Sukkur, Larkana, Shikarpur, Jacobabad, Khairpur, Ghotki, Kashmore, Kamber-Shahdadkot, and Qambar in northern Sindh.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to pay SEPCO bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Pay SEPCO electricity bill through JazzCash (Utility Bills → Electricity → SEPCO → 14-digit reference number), EasyPaisa, or any bank mobile app. Also payable at UBL, HBL, MCB, and National Bank branches.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the SEPCO helpline number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">SEPCO helpline is 118 from any landline in Sindh, or call 071-9210055 from mobile. For complaints, use the SEPCO complaint cell at 071-5613000. You can also register complaints online at sepco.com.pk.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I download a duplicate SEPCO bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. Visit pakistanbill.online/sepco-bill/, enter your 14-digit reference number, and click 'Download PDF' to save a duplicate copy of your SEPCO bill. The duplicate is valid for payment at any bank or retailer.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Why is my SEPCO bill not showing online?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">If your SEPCO bill is not loading, possible reasons: (1) wrong reference number entered, (2) bill not yet generated for current month — SEPCO generates bills 7–10 days before due date, (3) new connection not yet registered in the system, (4) reference number has fewer than 14 digits. Verify your reference number from a previous bill.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Is SEPCO the same as HESCO?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">No. SEPCO covers upper (northern) Sindh — Sukkur, Larkana, Khairpur. HESCO covers lower (southern) Sindh — Hyderabad, Karachi (parts), Mirpurkhas, Nawabshah. If you live in Hyderabad, your bill is HESCO, not SEPCO.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to apply for a new SEPCO connection?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Visit your nearest SEPCO circle office with CNIC, ownership/tenancy documents, and a filled A&AC Form-1 (available at sepco.com.pk). Connection fee for a single-phase domestic connection is Rs. 2,500–6,500 depending on load. New connections are typically activated within 30–45 days.</div></details>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-primary-900 mb-2">Check Your SEPCO Bill Now</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-700 mb-4 text-sm">Free, instant, no login required. Enter your 14-digit reference number.</p>
